op of the function, but this doesn't actually change what values get assigned—it just changes *when* they're assigned. The real issue is that moving these assignments earlier might cause them to execute before some prerequisite setup is complete, which could leave the rule in an inconsistent state when the instruction tries to use it. So the test setup is configuring which specific test case to run—test 238—and then executing the full test suite to see what fails. I need to find what test 238 actually does to understand why it's timing out.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2154,"cache_read_input_tokens":38112,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2154},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9896ccad-9b92-4563-9d8e-996a3d9d68c5","uuid":"cf148765-9495-47cb-878a-3c6e5b663bb7"}
